==English==
===Etymology===
Named after German [[mathematician]] [[w:Felix Klein|Felix Klein]] (1849-1925) who first described such a surface in 1882.  "[[bottle|Bottle]]" seems to have come from a [[misread]]ing or [[mistranslate|mistranslation]] of German [[Fläche]] as [[Flasche]] (the latter meaning bottle).
===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# {{topology}} A two-dimensional enclosed [[surface]] which doesn't have a distinct "[[inside]]" and "[[outside]]" (in a similar way that a [[Möbius strip]] has only one side).
